<paragraph id="14530B119201FFC6FF08FE44ED55FE58" blockId="6.[131,777,471,1485]" box="[132,277,471,497]" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B119201FFC6FF08FE65EDAAFA64" blockId="6.[131,777,471,1485]" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">Colony encrusting, multiserial, sheet-like, unilamellar. Autozooids longer than wide, ZL 354-597 μm (N colonies 4; N zooids 26; mean 446; SD 58 μm), ZW 231-355 μm (N colonies 4; N zooids 26; mean 288; SD 30 μm), the proximolateral margins typically concave and the distolateral margins convex with well-rounded distal ends. Frontal wall entirely lacking gymnocyst; cryptocyst forming most of the frontal surface, gently convex, depressed beneath the raised rims outlining the zooids, lacking paired tubercles at the distolateral corners, texture granular; cryptocystal pores not evident (quite possibly obscured by diagenetic neomorphism of the skeleton); opesiules located adjacent to the raised zooidal rim in the distal half of the zooid, long and narrow, curved, either a single pair or two pairs in which case the more proximal opesiules are shorter in length. Orifice semielliptical, wider than long, OL 44-52 μm (N colonies 2; N zooids 10; mean 47 μm; SD 3 μm), OW 89-109 μm (N colonies 2; N zooids 10; mean 97 μm; SD 7 μm), the proximal edge straight or slightly concave. Ovicells small, moderately raised, the ooecium rounded rectangular, wider than long, 84-97 µm long by 168-181 µm wide, calcification continuous with the cryptocyst of the distal zooid; orifices of ovicellate zooids significantly wider than those of non-ovicellate zooids, about 90 µm long by 175 µm wide. Avicularia absent in ovicellate zooids but present in all non-ovicellate zooids, located immediately distal of the orifice, oriented transversely, small, about 100-104 µm long by 64-89 µm wide, the opesia round and the rostrum rounded triangular in shape; presence of condyles or a pivotal bar uncertain. Ancestrula and early astogenetic stages not observed.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5CF6589A9201FFC6FF09FA60EE66F845" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="14530B119201FFC6FF09FA60ECACF9A2" blockId="6.[131,777,1523,2028]" box="[133,236,1523,1549]" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B119201FFC6FF08F980EF47F805" blockId="6.[131,777,1523,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">
As mentioned above, the lack of modern descriptions of species of putative 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929201FFC6FEEFF9A0ED94F9E5" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[355,468,1587,1612]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D7039201FFC6FEEFF9A0ED94F9E5" box="[355,468,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">Micropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Late Cretaceous makes comparisons with the new species difficult. However, the Maastrichtian species 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929201FFC6FE54F9E0EC86F905" authority="(Marsson, 1887)" baseAuthorityName="Marsson" baseAuthorityYear="1887" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="biforis">
<emphasis id="2698D7039201FFC6FE54F9E0EED0F925" box="[472,656,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">Micropora biforis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09201FFC6FD13F9E1ECFEF905" author="MARSSON T. F." pageId="6" pageNumber="519" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref7680" refString="MARSSON T. F. 1887. - Die Bryozoen der weissen Schreibkreide der Insel Rugen. Palaeontologische Abhandlungen 4: 1 - 112. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 11316917" type="journal article" year="1887">Marsson, 1887</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="6CFB4B819201FFC6FE9CF901ED39F905" box="[272,377,1682,1708]" name="Germany" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">Germany</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="6CFB4B819201FFC6FE3AF901EE2CF905" box="[438,620,1682,1708]" name="Netherlands" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">the Netherlands</collectingCountry>
has a pair of rounded opesiules close to mid-length, whereas the opesiules of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929201FFC6FF5DF940ED2FF945" authorityName="Taylor &amp; Villier" authorityYear="2022" box="[209,367,1746,1772]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="mikesmithi">
<emphasis id="2698D7039201FFC6FF5DF940ED2FF945" box="[209,367,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">M. mikesmithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more slit-shaped, located further distally and consist of two pairs. In both Marsson’s species and 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929201FFC6FF34F881EE3CF885" authority="Brydone, 1936" authorityName="Brydone" authorityYear="1936" box="[184,636,1810,1836]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="multicrescens">
<emphasis id="2698D7039201FFC6FF34F881ED82F885" box="[184,450,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">Micropora multicrescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09201FFC6FE40F881EE3CF885" author="BRYDONE R. M." box="[460,636,1810,1836]" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" pagination="61 - 90" refId="ref7072" refString="BRYDONE R. M. 1936. - Further Notes on New or Imperfectly Known Chalk Polyzoa. Part 3. Privately published, London: 61 - 90." type="book chapter" year="1936">Brydone, 1936</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, there is no indication of the presence of avicularia distal to the autozooids. 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929201FFC6FF50F8C1EE24F8C5" authority="(Hagenow, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="Hagenow" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[220,612,1873,1900]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="mohli">
<emphasis id="2698D7039201FFC6FF50F8C1EDD4F8C2" box="[220,404,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">Micropora mohli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09201FFC6FE29F8C1EE1CF8C5" author="HAGENOW F. V." box="[421,604,1873,1900]" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" refId="ref7525" refString="HAGENOW F. V. 1851. - Die Bryozoen der Maastrichter Kreidebildung. Fischer, Cassel, 111 p." type="book" year="1851">Hagenow, 1851</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
resembles the new species but the avicularia are directed almost distally in contrast to the transverse orientation seen in 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929201FFC6FDE8F801EEBFF802" authorityName="Taylor &amp; Villier" authorityYear="2022" box="[612,767,1937,1963]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="mikesmithi">
<emphasis id="2698D7039201FFC6FDE8F801EEBFF802" box="[612,767,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">M. mikesmithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B119201FFC6FF17F822EE66F845" blockId="6.[131,777,1523,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">
Colonies of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929201FFC6FEAAF821ED86F862" authorityName="Taylor &amp; Villier" authorityYear="2022" box="[294,454,1969,1995]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="mikesmithi">
<emphasis id="2698D7039201FFC6FEAAF821ED86F862" box="[294,454,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">M. mikesmithi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
encrust shells of the bivalve 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929201FFC6FF0AF842EE62F845" authority="(Lamarck, 1806)" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1806" box="[134,546,2001,2028]" class="Bivalvia" family="Gryphaeidae" genus="Pycnodonte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vesiculare">
<emphasis id="2698D7039201FFC6FF0AF842ED24F842" box="[134,356,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="519">Pycnodonte vesiculare</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09201FFC6FEFCF842EE5AF845" author="LAMARCK J. - B." box="[368,538,2001,2028]" pageId="6" pageNumber="519" pagination="156 - 166" refId="ref7586" refString="LAMARCK J. - B. 1806. - Suite des memoires sur les fossiles des environs de Paris. Annales du Museum d'Histoire naturelle 8: 156 - 166. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 14758222" type="journal article" year="1806">Lamarck, 1806</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
